Hollywood’s A-listers flocked to the first major awards show of the year, the Golden Globes 2023, despite a series of scandals swirling around its organisers about lack of diversity and allegations of ethical lapses. Given this, all eyes were on which Hollywood stars would attend the Globes. While many heavy hitters like Steven Spielberg, Rihanna and Brad Pitt were in attendance, other big names including Cate Blanchett, Kevin Costner, Zendaya and Amanda Seyfried. Brendan Fraser and Tom Cruise also didn’t attend the gala.  ALSO SEE: WATCH: Charlize Theron ‘on the toilet, on the toilet, on the toilet’ The Fabelmans won for best drama film and best director, putting Steven Spielberg’s semi-autobiographical movie in good position ahead of the Oscars on March 12. The Banshees of Inisherin won for best comedy film. This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window. This is a modal window. This modal can be closed by pressing the Escape key or activating the close button.